30/04/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov returned from Paris on Thursday (29 April) and said that France had offered to lend 400m euros to help modernise the army and purchase new equipment. 
If the finance ministry approves the loan, the funds could be expected in June. 
Svinarov also said that Bulgaria is seeking a contract to provide weapons for the new Iraqi Army. 
(Standart, Sega - 30/04/04)
